Prerequisites
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Perl >= 5.8 (http://perl.org)

The following 3rd party perl modules are required. The versions are
recommendations. The module lists below are more or less comprehensive.
The required Perl core modules have not been listed below.

Note that some Unix/Linux distributions may pack some of the Perl core modules
separately and require them to be installed separately. This means also that
the actual installation procedure may vary greatly for each distro.

The FreeBSD and Ubuntu details further below are likely to be inaccurate and
missing some steps. The information was mainly gathered to aid the current
and future clive package maintainers to get started. Note that the CPAN
installation steps exist only if the distro does not have the equivalent
package or a version available. For example, the 3.x of WWW::Curl kept
refusing to work with the current version of clive.

Note that the Clipboard module is OPTIONAL.

* Config::Tiny/2.12           * BerkeleyDB/0.34
* WWW::Curl/4.05              * URI::Escape/3.29
* HTML::TokeParser/2.37       * Clipboard/0.09
* IO::Pager/0.05              * XML::Simple/2.18
* Term::ProgressBar/2.09      * Expect


Installation
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Extract:
    % tar xvjf clive-$release.tar.bz2 && cd clive-$release

Run:
    % ./clive [option]... [URL]...

Getting started:
    % ./clive --manual

The manual page is written in Perl Pod markup language and it is embedded
in the script file. See "perldoc perlpod" for more info. For example:
    % pod2man clive > clive.1


Installation: FreeBSD (7.0)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

From the ports:
  * devel/p5-Term-ProgressBar
  * databases/p5-BerkeleyDB
  * security/p5-Digest-SHA
  * textproc/p5-XML-Simple
  * devel/p5-Config-Tiny
  * www/p5-HTML-Parser
  * devel/p5-IO-Pager
  * net/p5-URI
  * ftp/curl
  * lang/p5-Expect
  -- Optional:
  * x11/p5-Clipboard

From CPAN:
  * WWW::Curl


Installation: Ubuntu (Hardy)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

From apt: # Typically: "sudo apt-get install $module"
  * libterm-progressbar-perl
  * libcurl4-openssl-dev
  * libhtml-parser-perl
  * libconfig-tiny-perl
  * libberkeleydb-perl
  * libdigest-sha-perl
  * libxml-simple-perl
  * libfile-spec-perl
  * liburi-perl 
  * perl-doc
  * libexpect-perl
  -- Optional:
  * xclip (for Clipboard module below)

From CPAN: # Typically: "sudo cpan install $module"
  * WWW::Curl
  * IO::Pager
  -- Optional:
  * Clipboard
